   "hider_text": "The tide pulls at the edge of the cliff, not with sound but with pressure — a slow, steady breath against the stone. Salt hangs in the air like dust, thick and old.  \n\nBelow, the roots of ancient pines curve into the slope, hollowed by wind and time. They don’t grow straight; they twist, like fingers reaching for something unseen. When the wind stirs",
   "seeker_text": "The smell of wet concrete after rain.  \n\nNot the sharp, metallic kind from a storm drain, but the deep, slow breath of pavement soaking up water—cool and porous, like the earth exhaling through its skin. It clings to the soles of your shoes, lingers in the hollows of your pockets, and when you close your eyes, it’s the first thing you notice",
