   "hider_text": "The salt falls slow on the windowpane, like a breath held too long. Outside, the wind carries something metallic—old metal, rusted hinges, the sigh of a ship’s bell buried in the earth. The apartment doesn’t have a view, but the walls remember. They press against the cold, and inside, the air thickens with the scent of damp wool and forgotten keys.\n\nA",
