  {
   "round": 6,
   "hider_text": "The salt has settled in the cracks of the old stone wall, like a memory that won’t dissolve. I walk past the rusted gate where the wind hums through the metal, and the sound isn’t loud—just low, like the breath of something deep and patient. There’s a patch of moss that grows in the shadow of the overhang, green but not bright, as if it",
   "seeker_text": "The way your toes curl slightly when you’re sitting still in a dark room—no movement, no thought, just the tiny, involuntary arch of muscle beneath your socks. Not a sensation, not a memory, but a quiet echo of gravity pulling at the edges of stillness. It happens every time, and only you notice. A small, unnoticed anchor in the dark.",
